The paper discusses the LoRa physical layer technology, which is related to wireless communication and networking. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses the performance of LoRa receiver algorithms, which is related to network performance evaluation, making cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) another likely category. The paper proposes compensation methods for carrier frequency offset and sampling frequency offset, which are related to control and system theory, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible category. The paper also discusses the demodulation schemes and software-defined radio implementation, which are related to communication and signal processing, making cs.COMM (Signal Processing and Communications) and cs.EM (Electromagnetics) possible categories.
